<div class="neighborhoods">
  <h2> Mexico City is a city of different neighborhoods as unique as cities themselves. Here's our guide to the most iconic
    neighborhoods in the city. Tip: Take Uber to get you to and from these neighborhoods.</h2>
    <div class="polanco">
      <h3>Polanco is known as the most elite and trendy neighborhood in the city. Many large hotels reside here as well as some
      of the city's hottest restaurants and clubs. Take a stroll the park, grab a coffee and do some shopping here.</h3>
      <p>Recommendations:</p>
      <p>Seafood: La Trainera Polanco</p>
      <p>Typical Mexican: Hacienda de los Morales</p>
      <p>High End: Pujol (Top 17th Restaurant in the world)</p>
      <p>Best quick bite: Sushi Itto (Mexican sushi is a genre of its own)</p>
  </div>
<br>
    <div class='centro'>
      <h3>Centro Historico or the Historic Center is a must see. The zocalo or plaza is where dancers, musicians abound. </h3>
      <p>Top picks for centro historico:</p>
      <p>Visit the cathedral.</p>
      <p>Walk through the former Aztec pyramid behind the Catheral.</p>
      <p>Visit the Blue Tile building (La Casa del Azulejos). It's the original Sanborns, a classic breakfast restaurant and eat the enchiladas suizas.</p>
      <p>Get a view from the rooftop of the zocalo. Our recommendation: Visit the hotel Zocalo Central for a drink on their rooftop.</p>
    </div>
